The RSM can establish the settings of the input variables and optimize a single or a series of outputs. Also, within certain constraints, RSM optimizes the optimal output responses by maximizing or decreasing process parameters. RSM was used in this work to create a predictive model that consists of a set of quadratic algebraic equations. The data collected during the experimental phase was used for the modeling. The second-degree polynomial expression denotes the RSM-based model:5y=d0+∑n=1kdixi+∑i=1k∑j≥ikdijxixj+ϵ.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
